          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Perfect! I've successfully added all the necessary dependencies to the Cargo.toml file. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Dependencies Added\n\n**Normal dependencies:**\n- `circular = \"0.3\"` - Circular buffer library used by the reader implementations\n- `nom = \"7\"` - Parser combinators library used throughout the code for parsing PCAP/PCAPNG formats\n- `rusticata-macros = \"4\"` - Provides the `align32` macro used in serialization and parsing\n\n**Optional dependency:**\n- `cookie-factory = { version = \"0.3\", optional = true }` - Serialization library enabled by the `serialize` feature\n\nThe dependencies section was completely empty in the original Cargo.toml, which would have caused compilation errors since the source code imports from these external crates:\n- `nom` is used in multiple modules (pcapng, pcap, serialize)\n- `rusticata_macros` is used for the `align32` macro in enhanced packet parsing and serialization\n- `circular` is used for circular buffers in the reader implementations\n\nThe `serialize` feature already correctly references `cookie-factory` as an optional dependency, so the binding is now in place.\n\nAll other dependencies (dev-dependencies like criterion, hex-literal, and pprof) were already properly configured.\n\nSources:\n- [pcap-parser 0.16.0 - Docs.rs](https://docs.rs/pcap-parser/0.16.0)\n- [crates.io: Rust Package Registry](https://crates.io/crates/pcap-parser)",
